Starfleet Epsilon Prime Shipyards


- User Registration:
As a user, I want to register an account with a unique username and password.
Priority: High

- User Authentication:
As a user, I want a secure authentication process using email verification.
Priority: High

- Profile Management:
As a user, I want the ability to update my profile information, including email and profile picture.
Priority: Medium

- Product Catalog:
As an admin, I want to manage a catalog of products with details such as name, description, and price.
Priority: High

- Order Placement:
As a customer, I want to be able to add products to my shopping cart and place an order.
Priority: High

- Payment Integration:
As a user, I want a secure and seamless payment integration for processing orders.
Priority: High

- Inventory Management:
As an admin, I want to track and manage product inventory, including stock levels and restocking alerts.
Priority: Medium

- Order History:
As a customer, I want to view my order history and track the status of my shipments.
Priority: Medium

- Feedback and Reviews:
As a user, I want to leave feedback and reviews for products I have purchased.
Priority: Low

- Perform Mission:
As a user, I want to perform a mission
Priority: Low

- Supply Chain Management:
As a logistics specialist, I want an efficient system for managing the supply chain, tracking the availability of resources, and ensuring timely deliveries.
Priority: Medium

- Construction Progress Tracking:
As a project manager, I want a comprehensive dashboard to track the progress of starship construction, including key milestones and potential bottlenecks.
Priority: High

- Customizable Reporting System:
As a manager, I want a customizable reporting system to generate detailed reports on resource utilization, project timelines, and overall shipyard efficiency.
Priority: High

- Collaborative Starship Design Platform:
As a starship engineer, I want a collaborative platform that enables real-time sharing and discussion of starship design ideas among team members.
Priority: High
